The paper discusses the vulnerability of EEG-based BCIs, specifically spellers, to adversarial attacks. This topic falls under the sub-category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC), as well as computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning algorithms in EEG-based BCIs, which falls under the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper highlights the potential consequences of these attacks in clinical applications, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
